      • setJdbcType

        public void setJdbcType(int type,
                        String numericEncoding)
        Set the type for this column based on the incoming parameters. If a target platform doesn't understand a "fixed decimal" type, then the numericEncoding parameter allows us to override the JDBC type received from the database and cause the fields to be formatted as specified (i.e. as a Float or String).
        Parameters:
        type - the java.sql.Types jdbc type for this column.
        numericEncoding - encode numeric (fixed decimal) types as Float or String
